data.name: Space Needle
data.description: The Space Needle is an observation tower in Seattle, Washington, a landmark of the Pacific Northwest, and an icon of Seattle. It was built in the Seattle Center for the 1962 World's Fair, which drew over 2.3 million visitors, when nearly 20,000 people a day used its elevators.

value.name: Nickname for space needle
value.text: the original nickname of the space needle was "the space cage.". the original name of the restaurant was "eye of the needle.". from the time of its construction, the space needle has always had a light atop the structure. the most recent version is the legacy light, first illuminated on new year's eve 1999/2000.

value.name: Who commissioned the space needle
value.text: the space needle was commissioned as part of the 1962 world's fair hosted in seattle. the theme of that year's fair was "century 21," which helps to explain the space needle's futuristic design. edward carlson came up with the original designs, which had a top that resembled a floating balloon.

value.name: Downtown seattle by the space needle
value.text: built for the 1962 world’s fair, the space needle is located just north of the downtown area at seattle center. upon opening, it drew over 2 million visitors - nearly 20,000 per day during the world's fair!

value.name: Why is the space needle important

value.name: What does the space needle have inside of it
value.text: making the world better, one answer at a time. inside the space needle is the observation deck which is the very top floor. the second floor of the space need which is directly under neath that is a restaurant, that has a moving floor that goes in circle, so while you eat you get the entire view of seattle.

value.name: 12 Flag Space Needle Raising
value.text: The Seahawks' 12 MAN Flag was risen atop the Space Needle on the Friday before the game against the Washington Redskins.

value.name: How tall is the space needle with the antenna and spire
value.text: once the tallest structure west of the mississippi river, it is 605 ft (184 m) high, 138 ft (42 m) wide, and weighs 9,550 tons.

value.name: Where is the space needle in washington seattle
value.text: the space needle is a landmark of the pacific northwest and an icon of downtown seattle. it was built in the seattle center for the 1962 world's fair. today, nearly 20,000 people ride its elevators every 24 hours.

value.name: When was the space needle built in gatlinburg
value.text: the gatlinburg space needle, which originally opened in 1970, is probably the most iconic attraction in gatlinburg, tn. the space needle towers high over the parkway at a height of 407 feet and offers visitors the chance to view the smoky mountains from a 360 degree platform.

value.name: Did lightning hit the space needle
value.text: during an afternoon storm, lightning hit the space needle, lighting up the observation tower. twenty-five lightning rods, including the spire itself, scatter the roof of the needle in an attempt to protect the building from lightning strikes, according to the space needle website.
